Document Object Model

DOM is a tree like structure where each element is represented as a node in the tree. DOM helps in manipulating the structure of page/element. Such as applying styles to the element, removing styles from the element etc. New elements can also be added to or removed from the DOM tree.

Types of Nodes in the DOM tree:


1. Element Node
2. text node
3. comment node
4. attribute node


DOM representation

<html>
	<head>
		<title>My Title</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>My Header</h1>
		<a href="#">My Link</a>
	</body>
</html>




DOM : dom or document object model is a w3c standard which helps the programmer to change the structure of the page and/or its elements.




document object properties:


1. anchors

e.g
a=document.anchors;

2. links
3. body
4. forms
5. head
6. images

document.images[0].src="";

7. scripts
8. title



Functions:


1. getElementById('id')
2. getElementsByTagName('tag')
3. getElementsByClassName('class')
4. setAttribute('attribute','value');
	e.g. document.getElementById('heading').setAttribute('class','heading');
5. getAttribute('attribute');
6. createElement('tag');





